description:
Desiring to become an alicorn like Princess Twilight Sparkle, the unicorn Zappityhoof and her compatriots, Decepticolt and Goldcap used a spell to steal Rainbow Dash's wings and mixed them into a potion in that would give them wings. The three headed into the forest to wait for the potion to stabilize when they spotted a camouflaged Twilight Sparkle and captured her and Rainbow Dash. While the two were incarcerated, she and her friends questioned Twilight's worthiness and whether or not her own wings hadn't been stolen from another pegasus like Rainbow Dash. The trio waited for the potion's completion, unaware the two captives had merged their abilities and escaped, knocking out all three and claiming the potion for the pegasus.

The three attempted to flee only to be blasted by the alicorn, who temporarily takes away their magic as punishment, leaving them to walk home as the three lament the loss of both their abilities and ascension.
name: Zappityhoof

description: A male unicorn who, along with his companions Zappityhoof and Goldcap steal Rainbow Dash's wings with the use of a spell and mix them into a potion to become alicorns like Twilight Sparkle. He and his team are almost ambushed by the princess and their victim but manage to turn the tables on the two, capturing them in a net. The three are surprised however when the two captives combine their abilities and take back the potion. As punishment the three are stripped of their magical abilities which would not return for an unspecified amount of time. Decepticolt, along with his friends are allowed to go free, albeit lamenting their defeat, going so far as to call Twilight Sparkle a "Snotty Alicorn".
name: Decepticolt

deck: A member of a trio of unicorns that steal Rainbow Dash's wings.
description:
Desiring to become an alicorn like Princess Twilight Sparkle, the unicorn Goldcap and her compatriots used a spell to steal Rainbow Dash's wings and mixed them into a potion that would give them wings. The three headed into the forest to wait the sunrise for the potion to stabilize when they spotted a camouflaged Twilight Sparkle and captured her and Rainbow Dash. While incarcerated, Twilight attempted to reason with the three that stealing the wings wasn't right. Goldcap, however, rebuked her and took the lead in questioning Twilight's worthiness and whether or not her own wings hadn't been stolen from another pegasus like Rainbow Dash. The trio waited for the potion's completion, unaware the two captives had merged their abilities and escaped, knocking out all three and claiming the potion for the pegasus.

The three attempted to flee only to be blasted by the alicorn, who temporarily takes away their magic for an unspecified amount of time as punishment, leaving them to walk home as the three lament the loss of both their abilities and ascension.
name: Goldcap

deck: New member of the Suicide Squad who is capable of very limited prescience
description:
Origin

Very little is known about Afterthought. He was the subject of an experiment that created a quantum window to the immediate future in his mind; whether his participation was voluntary is unclear. He may not be a criminal, or at least has never been arrested; despite this, he was invited to join, or volunteered for, the Suicide Squad.

Creation

Afterthought was created by Steve Orlando and ACO. He made his first appearance in Midnighter #9

Major Story Arcs

Midnighter

After Midnighter steals a valuable pistol from a Suicide Squad installation, Afterthought is sent alongside Deadshot and Harley Quinn to recover it. Due to his powers, he is a match for Midnighter and easily defeats him in combat. He later confronts Midnighter again, but Midnighter is able to overwhelm and defeat him. He is taken into custody by Spyral.

Powers and Abilities

Afterthought's brain has been infused with an experimental system that allows him to observe events five seconds into the future, which makes him a formidable opponent in combat. He is also a skilled hand-to-hand combatant.
name: Afterthought

deck: Frank is a member of the Howling Commandos Monster-Squad, and is a clone of the original Frankenstein Monster. He is smarter than the original and has a giant fist on a chain that he can fire
description:
Origin

Frank, as he likes to be called, is a cloned replica of the original Frankenstein Monster. He has become a part of the SHIELD team known as the Howling Commandos.

Creation

Frankenstein's Monster (Clone) was created by Keith Giffen and Eduardo Franisco and first appeared in Nick Fury's Howling Commandos issue 1 (2005).

Major Story Arcs

Howling Commandos

Frankenstein's Cloned Monster had become a part of the monster unit known as the Howling Commandos. He was super strong, but was also very intelligent compared to his original counterpart. "Frank", as he monster would like to be called, joined the team on a number of missions and even fought Merlin. The team eventually disbanned and Frank was not seen again.


More recently, a new monster-team of Howling Commandos was assembeled, but Frank was not a part of the line-up.
name: Frankenstein's Monster (Clone)

deck: Zombie was an unknown reanimated corps that was part of the Monster-team known as the Howling Commandos.
description:
Origin

Nothing is known about the person that Zombie was before he became reanimated and was recruited for SHIELD. The organization was however trying to find this out.

Creation

Zombie (John Doe) was created by Keith Giffen and Eduardo Franciso and first appeared in Nick Fury's Howling Commandos issue 1 (2005). He is not to be mistaken for the more well-known Zombie, Simon Garth.

Major Story Arcs

Howling Commandos

Zombie was recruited into the Howling Commandos, a team of supernatural monsters that became a special task force for SHIELD. Zombie had a number of missions with the team before they disbannded.

More recently, a new team of Howling Commandos was created by SHIELD. Zombie John Doe was not part of the line-up.
name: Zombie (John Doe)
